# Competition Blog Frontend Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the development of a high-performance, SEO-optimized sports blog website using Next.js.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup
- [NEW] Initialize Next.js project with App Router and TypeScript.
- [NEW] Configure global styles and theme using Vanilla CSS Variables (Glassmorphism, Dark Mode support).
- [NEW] Set up core directory structure:
  - `components/`: UI components (Atomic design)
  - `hooks/`: Custom React hooks
  - `lib/`: Utility functions and shared constants
  - `services/`: API client for the Go backend
  - `app/`: Next.js App Router pages

### Design System
- Implement a premium sports-themed design system.
- Colors: Deep navy, vibrant neon green/gold accents, and sleek grays.
- Typography: Inter or Montserrat for a modern feel.
- Components: Animated cards, real-time score widgets, and interactive blog layouts.

### Features
- **Homepage**: Hero section with featured matches, latest news grid, and category filtering.
- **Match Center**: A dedicated area for real-time scores (mocked initially for later Go backend integration).
- **SEO Library**: Centralized metadata management for posts and pages.
- **Editor Experience**: Implementation of a clean UI for content creators.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build`: Verify production build stability.
- `npx tsc`: Type check all files.

### Manual Verification
- Verify responsive layouts on desktop and mobile.
- Check lighthouse scores for SEO and Performance.
- Test real-time score updates simulation.
